data.title: Josh Homme joins Eagles Of Death Metal onstage at London gig with Alex Turner in crowd – watch
data.meta_description: NME catches up with Brody Dalle at the NME Awards 2014 with Austin, Texas about playing new tracks and Distillers' music live and touring with Queens Of The Stone Age.
data.text:
Eagles Of Death Metal performed live at London’s Koko on Wednesday night (June 17), with Queens Of The Stone Age frontman Josh Homme playing drums for the show.

Homme originally formed the group with Jesse Hughes in 1998, but rarely plays live with the group due to other band commitments. Having recently announced their new album ‘Zipper Down’, Homme, Hughes and co played a set that drew from their previous three albums, plus new single ‘Complexity’ and a cover of Stealers Wheel’s ‘Stuck In The Middle With You’.

SEE ALSO: Josh Homme’s 10 Finest Moments

Reports from the show state that Arctic Monkeys singer Alex Turner was among those in the attendance, as were Miles Kane, Iggy Pop and former Guns N’ Roses bassist Duff McKagan.
